        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 9 at 12:31AM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 1230 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles east of Panhandle, moving southwest at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pampa, Panhandle, Claude, White Deer, Groom, Kingsmill, Washburn, and
Goodnight.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
